{
 "name": "RPlog_Reflections_and_Revelations",
 "title": "Reflections and Revelations",
 "summary": "At dawn in the barracks, Paul Nighman sits cradling Shenner's guitar and softly sings a sad, yearning folk love song -- a lament of being lost without a beloved -- as the sleeping Jedi Jessalyn Valios wakes to his voice and the golden morning light. Moved by the song clearly meant for her, Jessalyn rises and the two share a tender, halting exchange of touches and quiet reassurances, Paul promising 'this is no Palahni' as they reaffirm the fragile, growing bond between them. A soft kiss and a blush mark the quiet revelation of their feelings, the early light closing on a moment of intimacy and hope.",
